== History ==
Ōmuro Park is situated on a plateau at an elevation of 130 meters on the southern slope of Mount Akagi<ref name="ze" />. The area is notable for the {{ill|Ōmuro Kofun Group (Maebashi)|ja|大室古墳群 (前橋市)|12=draft}}—a cluster of kofun (ancient Kofuns)—that underwent some of the earliest academic archaeological investigations in Japan. In 1878, the {{ill|Mae Futago Kofun|ja|前二子古墳|12=draft}}, believed to be the burial site of Toyokuninomikoto, was excavated. Artifacts discovered in the stone chambers attracted widespread attention at the time.

