== History == Ōmuro Park is situated on a plateau at an elevation of 130 meters on the southern slope of Mount Akagi<ref name="ze" />. The area is notable for the {{ill|Ōmuro Kofun Group (Maebashi)|ja|大室古墳群 (前橋市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmuro Kofun Group (Maebashi)|qq=}}—a cluster of kofun (ancient Kofuns)—that underwent some of the earliest academic archaeological investigations in Japan. In 1878, the [[:en:Maefutago Kofun|Mae Futago Kofun]], believed to be the burial site of Toyokuninomikoto, was excavated. Artifacts discovered in the stone chambers attracted widespread attention at the time.
Plans to develop the area as Ōmuro Park began in the late Shōwa period, led by Gunma Prefecture's parks and cultural heritage departments. In 1989, the Ōmuro Park Historic Site Development Committee was formed, and archaeological surveys commenced in 1991. Over the next six years, multiple mounds were investigated, including the [[:en:Maefutago Kofun|Mae Futago Kofun]], [[:en:Ushirofutago Kofun|Ushiro Futago Kofun]], [[:en:Nakafutago Kofun|Naka Futago Kofun]], and {{ill|Sho Futago Kofun|ja|小二子古墳|1=Sho Futago Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sho Futago Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Sho Futago Kofun|qq=}}. The park now encompasses a 500m x 1000m area, featuring national historic sites, remnants of ancient mansions, Edo-period {{ill|Akagigata folk houses|ja|赤城型民家|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akagigata folk houses|qq=}}, and reconstructed dwellings from the Kofun period.
== Features == The park includes: * {{ill|Ōmuro Kofun Group (Maebashi)|ja|大室古墳群 (前橋市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmuro Kofun Group (Maebashi)|qq=}} * {{ill|Umeki Ruins|ja|梅木遺跡|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Umeki Ruins|qq=}} (remains of a clan mansion) * Folk House Garden - featuring the {{ill|Former Sekine Family Residence|ja|旧関根家住宅|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Former Sekine Family Residence|qq=}} (a Maebashi City-designated Important Cultural Property) and ancient dwellings.
<gallery> File:Maefutago-kofun 2.jpg|[[:en:Maefutago Kofun|Mae Futago Kofun]] File:Nakafutago-kofun 4.jpg|[[:en:Nakafutago Kofun|Naka Futago Kofun]] File:Ushirofutago-kofun 1.jpg|[[:en:Ushirofutago Kofun|Ushiro Futago Kofun]] File:Shofutago-kofun 1.jpg|{{ill|Sho Futago Kofun|ja|小二子古墳|1=Sho Futago Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sho Futago Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Sho Futago Kofun|qq=}} File:Omuro Park Minka-en 2.jpg|Former Sekine Family Residence File:Omuro Park ancient houses.jpg|Ancient dwellings File:Goryo-numa.jpg|Goryō Marsh File:Konara in Omuro Park.jpg|Konara oak in Ōmuro Park (designated as a Natural Monument by Maebashi City) </gallery>
== Access == * 3.6 km from the {{ill|Hashie Smart Interchange|ja|波志江スマートインターチェンジ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hashie Smart Interchange|qq=}} on the [[:en:Kita-Kantō Expressway|Kita-Kantō Expressway]] (10 minutes by car). * 5 km from the {{ill|Isesaki Interchange|ja|伊勢崎インターチェンジ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isesaki Interchange|qq=}} on the Kita-Kantō Expressway (10 minutes by car). * 10 minutes by taxi from [[:en:Ōgo Station|Ōgo Station]] on the {{ill|Jōmō Electric Railway|ja|上毛電気鉄道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōmō Electric Railway|qq=}}. * 20 minutes by taxi from [[:en:Isesaki Station|Isesaki Station]] on the [[:en:Ryōmō Line|Ryōmō Line]].
